+# GitHub implementation backlog
+
+These work items should exist as GitHub issues after repository bootstrap. They are ordered by dependency, not by visual prominence.
+
+## 1. Complete the reference-repository migration inventory
+
+**Outcome:** Create a commit-pinned manifest mapping the current `hotel-wage-hour` corpus, data, calculators, routes, tests, research memos, and generated artifacts into the v2 object graph.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- inventory every tracked file at the audited reference commit
+- classify each item as migrate, transform, retain temporarily, archive, or discard
+- map current URLs to target URLs and redirects
+- map data fields to source, rule, change, jurisdiction, tool, and public-content entities
+- identify calculator functions, parameters, fixtures, and unresolved gaps
+- record owners, review dates, volatility, and source completeness
+- produce a dual-run and rollback plan
+
+## 2. Establish the canonical authority and rule registry
+
+**Outcome:** Replace page-embedded legal propositions with versioned source, passage, rule, and interpretation entities.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- stable IDs and effective intervals
+- immutable source versions and passage locators
+- authority hierarchy and supersession relationships
+- attorney/editorial approval states
+- disclosed ambiguity and competing interpretations
+- dependency events that identify affected public pages and product outputs
+
+## 3. Migrate the public authority layer with URL and SEO parity
+
+**Outcome:** Render the existing substantive corpus through the v2 evidence standard without losing public URLs, citations, accessibility, or search equity.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- canonical URL inventory and one-to-one redirects
+- structured issue, jurisdiction, development, methodology, and tool records
+- preserved titles, descriptions, headings, canonical tags, and structured data where appropriate
+- source lineage, reviewed dates, and revision history visible on every substantive page
+- sitemap, robots, feed, search index, and internal links validated
+- representative pages pass side-by-side editorial and accessibility review
+
+## 4. Extract and validate deterministic tool logic
+
+**Outcome:** Move calculator and audit logic into versioned, testable services independent of interface components.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- input and output schemas
+- applicability predicates and branch trace
+- rule-version and source references
+- known-answer fixtures and boundary tests
+- assumption and missing-fact handling
+- explanation steps and limitations
+- save-to-matter contract
+- attorney approval, monitoring, and rollback plan
+
+## 5. Implement tenant, identity, privilege, and audit foundations
+
+**Outcome:** Establish the security plane before any non-public portfolio, matter, evidence, or decision data is used.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- SSO/MFA and tenant isolation
+- object-level authorization and privileged-matter controls
+- encrypted storage and secrets management
+- immutable security and product audit events
+- legal holds, retention, deletion, and export procedures
+- threat model, abuse cases, incident response, and recovery tests
+- no enterprise route publicly indexable or anonymously accessible
+
+## 6. Build property facts and jurisdiction applicability pilot
+
+**Outcome:** Produce reproducible property-level applicability for a contained Southern California pilot cluster.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- property, entity, brand/operator, workforce, payroll, benefits, and scheduling schemas
+- jurisdiction resolver with source and effective-date lineage
+- fact provenance, ownership, freshness, and unresolved-fact states
+- reproducible applicability evaluations for 3–7 pilot properties
+- property passports and change-to-portfolio reach
+- no silent defaults for missing material facts
+
+## 7. Build governed matters, decisions, controls, and evidence
+
+**Outcome:** Carry one material change from source to approved decision and operating proof without external reconstruction.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- matter scope, facts, assumptions, findings, tasks, owners, and due dates
+- versioned decision record with approvals and conditions
+- control objectives, implementations, tests, evidence, exceptions, and remediation
+- complete provenance snapshot
+- invalidation and revalidation when a dependent source, rule, fact, finding, control, or evidence record changes
+
+## 8. Production-readiness and release governance
+
+**Outcome:** Define and satisfy the gates required to move from prototype to controlled pilot and production.
+
+**Acceptance criteria:**
+
+- branch/ruleset protection and required checks
+- private vulnerability reporting, secret scanning, and push protection where available
+- WCAG 2.2 AA audit and assistive-technology testing
+- performance budgets and production observability
+- backup, recovery, resilience, and incident exercises
+- privacy, retention, privilege, and customer-data review
+- legal/editorial release authority and change-management procedure
+- repository made private before non-public information is introduced
