+# Implementation roadmap
+
+## Phase 0 — product and governance foundation
+
+Deliverables:
+
+- canonical object model and IDs
+- source and rule governance
+- tenant / privilege architecture
+- content migration inventory
+- calculation validation standard
+- design tokens and component library
+- analytics and audit-event taxonomy
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- legal, product, engineering, security, and editorial owners approve the contracts
+- no critical entity depends on unversioned free text
+
+## Phase 1 — authority graph
+
+Deliverables:
+
+- source registry and version acquisition
+- passage-level citations
+- canonical analysis CMS
+- jurisdiction and issue taxonomies
+- developments pipeline
+- public search and revision history
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- representative public content can be rendered from structured entities
+- a source change can identify affected rules and pages
+
+## Phase 2 — property applicability
+
+Deliverables:
+
+- tenant and property model
+- jurisdiction resolver
+- workforce segments
+- fact provenance and freshness
+- applicability engine
+- property passports
+- change-to-portfolio reach
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- pilot properties produce reproducible applicability evaluations
+- unresolved facts are explicit rather than defaulted silently
+
+## Phase 3 — matters and decisions
+
+Deliverables:
+
+- governed matter lifecycle
+- scenarios and findings
+- assignments and due dates
+- decision-record generation
+- approval and versioning
+- audit history
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- one material change can travel from source to approved decision without external reconstruction
+
+## Phase 4 — controls and evidence
+
+Deliverables:
+
+- control objectives and control registry
+- evidence requirements and collection
+- exceptions and remediation
+- assurance calendar
+- decision conditions linked to controls
+- revalidation engine
+
+Exit criteria:
+
+- an obligation can be traced to operating proof and open exceptions
+
+## Phase 5 — validated tools and integrations
+
+Priority integrations:
+
+- HRIS
+- payroll
+- timekeeping
+- benefits
+- scheduling
+- property master data
+- document/evidence storage
+- identity and access
+
+Tool release requirements:
+
+- legal specification
+- test fixtures
+- branch trace
+- source version linkage
+- save-to-matter output
+- monitoring and rollback
+
+## Phase 6 — scaled intelligence and AI
+
+Capabilities:
+
+- permission-aware grounded ask
+- automated change impact proposals
+- draft findings and control mappings
+- anomaly detection
+- portfolio forecasting
+- executive narrative generation
+
+AI remains assistive and governed; approved legal conclusions and decisions retain human ownership.
+
